@node .cost "distribution"

   This program is freely distributable. Distribution is allowed if
the following conditions are met:

1. Program and documentation must not be changed in any way,
   rchiving with an archiver, for which the
   corresponding unarchiver will work on any CPU type used in
   Amigas at the time of distribution.

2. Program, documentation and the icons for the program and the
   documentation must be distributed together.

3. The file names of the program, documentation must not be changed.

4. The source code CAN be used in any way but if used as part
   of commercial software Credit must be given.

@endnode
@node .intro "introduction"

   DWTwin is a program that is used to control TwinExpress v1.1
     outside of its enviroment using DirWork v2.1 (or a script)
     for transfering files between two Amigas via Null Modem cable.
     (pause - refill your lungs!)

   Basically I use Dirwork v2.1 for file managment and Twin Express
    for file transfer between my A600 & A500+(A570cd),I wanted both
    programs to work for each other. As you can see I have not got
    powerfull Amiga's with a hardrive and lots of memory, so Dopus,
    TwinOpus & SerNet is not an option.

   TwinExpress is very fast but is used in its own shell enviroment
    and you can not execute files in the shell only use twin commands.
    But you can pass a file with twin commands in, it then executes
    twin doing the commands in the file. DWTwin creates the command
    file(s) and passes them to twin.

   DirWork 2.1 is an excellent file managment and more, its ability
    to be configured in almost any way makes an perfect programming
    aid. DirWork is used to control DWTtwin, I have supplied a
    DirWork Config file (dwtwin.cfg) which can be loaded into DWork
    and used with some adjustment see @{"   installation    " link .install},
    or used as an example for the buttons for your own config.
    DWTwin can be used by a dos script ,but you could easly write
    a script to control twin express.

   DWTwin v2.0 is a simple program that controls scripts and twin
    express, I have included the 'C' Source that can be easly
    changed,expanded or included in another program to suit you
    for new programmers to the Amiga its a good example for
    control of scripts.

@endnode
@node .requires "system requirements"

   2 Amigas.

   Twin Express v1.11 or later.
   DirWork 2.1 (not needed but recommended).

   DWTwin is designed to be compatible with the amiga operating
   system from WB1.3 upwards.

   Note its only been tested on WB2.04 & WB2.05.

@endnode
@node .install "installation"


Quick installation notes:

  DWTwin can be placed anywhere.

  You must have T: assigned somewhere, ie:  assign T: ram:t

  DWTwin automatically creates any files needed in T:

  DWTwin uses T: to store script files,command files and log file.
  script files are no more than 100 bytes (3 files max)
  command files depend on what you want twin express to do.
  log file is the size of output from twin express and is changed
  each time command(s) are sent to twin express.

  -*- NOTE -*-  if you use the dirwork example config file
                dwtwin.cfg as it is - you must have DWTtwin
                in T: and Twin Express in DF0: ,The config
                file can be easly changed.

@endnode
@node .usage "usage"

       DirWork v2.1 - run as normal, then load dwtwin.cfg if not using
                      your own updated config.
                      load configuration editor on dwtwin.cfg to see
                      the buttons to change your config or (I have not
                      tried this) edit your config in a editor and copy
                      the lines in dwtwin.cfg that matter to your config.
                      Then edit your config using the configuration editor

       Twin Express - if you are using DirWork if you press the [CD]
                      Button then the [TwinExpress] button on the
                      remote computer to set twin to the current path,
                      else run twin as normal.

       DWTwin -  options -:

        Copy single file to remote returns output to T:dwt.log.

            In Dwork click on file then click on [TCopySingleFile]
             remember to run twin on other amiga.

               Dwtwin c <filename> <twinpath>

               filename = file to copy
               twinpath = twin express path (ie df0:c )


        Do any single command  returns output to T:dwt.log.

            In Dwork click on file then click on [TAnySingleCom]
             remember to run twin on other amiga.
              displays requester to enter command.

               Dwtwin o <twinpath>

               twinpath = twin express path (ie df0:c )


       Set change path (cd) to T:dwt.intcom

            In Dwork click on [TSetPathIntCom]
               Displays requester to enter path

                  Dwtwin P


       Set create directory to T:dwt.intcom

            In Dwork click on [TCrtDirIntCom]
               Displays requester to enter directory

                  Dwtwin d


       Set any command to T:dwt.intcom

            In Dwork click on [TSetAnyIntCom]
               Displays requester to enter command

                  Dwtwin x


       Clear T:dwt.intcom ready for next list of commands

            In Dwork click on [TResetIntCom]

                  Dwtwin n


       Set copy file(s) to T:dwt.intcom

            In Dwork select file or multiple files then click on
              [TCpyFileIntCom]
               shows message to confirm each file set in dwt.intcom

                  Dwtwin l <filename(s)>

                  filename(s) = file(s) to copy


       Execute internal command file T:dwt.intcom returns output T:dwt.log.

            In Dwork click on [TwinExeIntCom]
             remember to run twin on other amiga.

                  Dwtwin a <twinpath>

                  twinpath   = twin express path (ie df0:c )


       Set any command to your command file


            There is no Button in dwtwin.cfg for this command
             but you can create one like this:

            load DWork configuration editor and create new button
             call it for example [TAnyExtCom].
            Then select change Actions and enter these options:

            function: Run external program

            [       Program       ]
            [ df0:c/dwtwin f %p%f ]

            [ current source ]     [Selected Dirs & Selected Files]


            Displays requester to enter command.

                  Dwtwin f <extcomfile>

                  extcomfile = your own twin command file.


       Execute your own command file using twin returns output T:dwt.log.

            In Dwork click on commandfile then click on [TwinExeExtCom]
             remember to run twin on other amiga.

              Dwtwin e <extcomfile> <twinpath>

              extcomfile = your own twin command file.
              twinpath   = twin express path (ie df0:c )


       Additional button in dwtwin.cfg

       [ViewLog] - views logfile

       [ViewInt] - views internal logfile


       If you run DWTwin no options :

                  -------------------------------------------------------
                  DWTwin v2.0 - Mark Weller (c)1998
                  -------------------------------------------------------
                  Usage: DWTwin <option> [<filename/twinpath>]
                  -------------------------------------------------------
                  Remember to run TwinExpress on remote Computer
                  -------------------------------------------------------
                  Dwtwin c <filename> <twinpath>     :copy single file
                  Dwtwin e <ext com file> <twinpath> :execute    [extcom]
                  Dwtwin a <twinpath>                :execute    [intcom]
                  Dwtwin l <filename>                :copy file  [intcom]
                  Dwtwin d  uses internal requester  :create dir [intcom]
                  Dwtwin p  uses internal requester  :set path   [intcom]
                  Dwtwin n                           :reset intcom
                  Dwtwin x  uses internal requester  :any comnd  [intcom]
                  Dwtwin f <extcomfile> uses intreq  :any comnd  [extcom]
                  Dwtwin o <twinpath>   uses intreq  :any single command
                  -------------------------------------------------------


@endnode

